Comando netstat para verificar portas abertas

netstat -na | findstr 389

by powershell to list ports

get-netTCPConnection -state listen localport 53,389,88

LDAP UDP 389
Kerberos UDP 88
Global catalog TCP 3268
DNS TCP 53
RPC 135
SMB TCP 445

===========================================================================================

Exibir apenas as portas que estão “ouvindo”
netstat -a -n | find /i “listening”
